<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,304,768,794]" box="[189,304,768,794]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,304,768,794]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,768,794]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[187,1399,815,1087]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Among the species formerly ascribed to 
<taxonomicName authority="Reitter, 1877" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1877" box="[701,992,815,841]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[701,818,815,841]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Atritomus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter E." box="[831,992,815,841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="71 - 100" refId="ref6866" refString="Reitter E. 1877. Atritomus nov. gen. Tritomidarum. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 21 (2): 384. Reitter E. 1879. Bestimmungs-Tabellen der europaischen Coleopteren. I. Enthaltend die Familien: Cucujidae, Telmatophilidae, Tritomidae, Mycetaeidae, Endomychidae, Lyctidae und Sphindidae. Verhandlungen der kaiserlich-koniglichen zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 21: 71 - 100." type="journal article" year="1877">Reitter, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1878" box="[1020,1135,815,840]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Tritoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="univestris">
<emphasis box="[1020,1135,815,840]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">univestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ has been spelled as ‘ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[199,303,851,876]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="univestis">
<emphasis box="[199,303,851,876]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">univestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’by several authors (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jakobson G. G." box="[584,761,850,877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="1905 - 1915" refId="ref6402" refString="Jakobson G. G. 1915. Beetles of Russia and Western Europe. Devriena, St Petersburg (1905 - 1915). [In Russian.]" type="book chapter" year="1915">Jakobson 1915</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hetschko A." box="[771,950,850,876]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref6246" refString="Hetschko A. 1930. Fam. Mycetophagidae. In: Junk W. &amp; Schenkling S. (eds) Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 108: 1 - 26. W. Junk, Berlin." type="journal article" year="1930">Hetschko 1930</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Iablokoff-Khnzorian S. M." box="[960,1271,850,877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="173 - 174" refId="ref6283" refString="Iablokoff-Khnzorian S. M. 1976. Eulagius acernus Motschulsky - A misunderstooded species (Coleoptera, Mycetophagidae). Zoological Papers 17: 173 - 174." type="journal article" year="1976">Iablokoff-Khnzorian 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Although the original specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1878" box="[523,638,886,911]" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Tritoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="univestris">
<emphasis box="[523,638,886,911]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">univestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is incorrect in the Latin language [the linguistically correct term ‘ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[199,303,921,946]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="univestis">
<emphasis box="[199,303,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">univestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ means ‘uniformly dressed’], it must be preserved unaltered in accordance with Art. 32.3 of the 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[269,429,956,982]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" refId="ref6365" refString="ICZN (International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature). 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, as the provisions of Art. 32.5 are not met. Therefore, the name ‘ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[1224,1328,956,981]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Atritomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="univestis">
<emphasis box="[1224,1328,956,981]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">univestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is to be considered an incorrect subsequent spelling (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[766,909,991,1017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" refId="ref6365" refString="ICZN (International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature). 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: art. 33.3) and thus unavailable. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Erotylidae" genus="Tritoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="univestris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Tritoma univestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently accepted as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1845" box="[752,959,1026,1052]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acernus">
<emphasis box="[752,959,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Eulagius acernus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Iablokoff-Khnzorian S. M." box="[973,1286,1026,1052]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="173 - 174" refId="ref6283" refString="Iablokoff-Khnzorian S. M. 1976. Eulagius acernus Motschulsky - A misunderstooded species (Coleoptera, Mycetophagidae). Zoological Papers 17: 173 - 174." type="journal article" year="1976">Iablokoff-Khnzorian 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky N. B." pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="51 - 55" refId="ref6679" refString="Nikitsky N. B. 2008. Family Mycetophagidae Leach, 1915. In: Lobl I. &amp; Smetana A. (eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. 5. Tenebrionoidea: 51 - 55. Apollo Book, Stenstrup." type="book chapter" year="2008">Nikitsky 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky N. B." box="[261,325,1061,1087]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="27 - 33" refId="ref6722" refString="Nikitsky N. B. 2020. Family Mycetophagidae Leach, 1915. In: Iwan D. &amp; Lobl I. (eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Revised and Updated Second Edition: 27 - 33. Brill, Leiden / Boston." type="book chapter" year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1126,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky N. B." box="[351,540,1126,1153]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="27 - 33" refId="ref6722" refString="Nikitsky N. B. 2020. Family Mycetophagidae Leach, 1915. In: Iwan D. &amp; Lobl I. (eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. 5. Tenebrionoidea. Revised and Updated Second Edition: 27 - 33. Brill, Leiden / Boston." type="book chapter" year="2020">Nikitsky (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1845" box="[553,761,1126,1152]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Eulagius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acernus">
<emphasis box="[553,761,1126,1152]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Eulagius acernus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1063,1126,1152]" name="Armenia" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1205,1126,1152]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1217,1314,1126,1152]" name="Georgia" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, and in the southern part of European 
<collectingCountry box="[545,627,1162,1188]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Russia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
